limit.description: A limit on the number of objects to be returned. The default is 100.

after.description: A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

before.description: A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, beginning with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.
